==Surname== A grandparent of Jonas Lössl is [[German (people)|German]]. For this reason, his surname is written with "ö" instead of "ø" which is otherwise the normal spelling of this letter in the Danish language.<ref name="nullfuenfmixedzone">{{Cite web|url=http://www.nullfuenfmixedzone.de/die-nummer-1-der-grossen-stadt|title=Die Nummer 1 in der großen Stadt|author=Christian Karn|date=6 July 2016|accessdate=17 July 2016|language=de}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.swr.de/sport/der-neue-mainz-05-torwart-jonas-loessl-im-portraet/-/id=1208948/did=17738004/nid=1208948/128nx27/|title=Torwart Jonas Lössl ist von Mainz beeindruckt|date=7 July 2016|accessdate=17 July 2016|language=de}}</ref>
==Club career== ===FC Midtjylland=== A product of the [[FC Midtjylland]] football academy, Lössl made his [[Danish Superliga]] debut with [[FC Midtjylland]] in March 2010. He played a total number of 137 matches for the club.
===Guingamp=== On 5 June 2014, FC Midtjylland reported that they had sold Lössl to French football club, [[En Avant de Guingamp|Guingamp]].<ref>{{cite news|title=FCM sælger Jonas Lossl til Guingamp|url=https://www.tv3sport.dk/sport/fodbold/nyheder/fcm-saelger-jonas-lossl-til-guingamp|accessdate=13 September 2017|publisher=tv3sport.dk|date=5 June 2014}}</ref> After initially starting his first season as a backup keeper at the club, Lössl eventually established himself as the club's first-choice keeper in his two seasons at the club.
===Mainz 05=== On 16 June 2016, it was reported that Lössl was making a move to German club [[1. FSV Mainz 05|Mainz 05]]. The club cited that they intended Lössl to be the instant replacement for the club's previous keeper, [[Loris Karius]], who himself had just transferred to [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Transferchok: Jonas Lössl skifter til Bundesligaen|url=https://www.tv3sport.dk/sport/fodbold/nyheder/transferchok-jonas-lossl-skifter-til-bundesligaen|accessdate=13 September 2017|publisher=tv3sport.dk|date=16 June 2016}}</ref>
====Huddersfield Town (loan)==== After one season at Mainz, Lössl signed for [[Huddersfield Town F.C.|Huddersfield Town]] on a season-loan on 30 June 2017.<ref name="htafc.com">{{cite web|url=https://www.htafc.com/news/2017/june/loan-goalkeeper-jonas-lossl-joins-town/|title=Huddersfield Town LOAN: GOALKEEPER JONAS LÖSSL JOINS TOWN|publisher=}}</ref> On 12 August 2017, Lössl made his debut for Huddersfield in a 3–0 win against Crystal Palace.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2017/aug/12/crystal-palace-huddersfield-town-premier-league-match-report|title=Steve Mounié double gives Huddersfield perfect start against Crystal Palace|first=Paul Doyle at Selhurst|last=Park|date=12 August 2017|publisher=|via=The Guardian}}</ref>
===Huddersfield Town=== Following a successful loan spell in which he kept 10 Premier League clean sheets, Huddersfield activated a clause in Lössl's loan deal from Mainz, and signed him permanently for an undisclosed fee.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/43431813 |title=Jonas Lossl: Huddersfield Town to sign Mainz goalkeeper on permanent deal |publisher=BBC Sport |date=16 March 2018 |accessdate=31 May 2018}}</ref>
==International career== Lössl played 22 games for various Danish national youth teams, including 15 games for the [[Denmark under-21 national football team]].
He was called up to the senior [[Denmark national football team|Denmark]] squad in June 2015 for a friendly against [[Montenegro national football team|Montenegro]],<ref>{{cite news|title=Denmark 2–1 Montenegro|url=http://www.eurosport.co.uk/football/international-friendlies/2015/denmark-montenegro_mtc763517/live.shtml|accessdate=13 November 2015|publisher=eurosport.co.uk|date=8 June 2015}}</ref> and again for the [[UEFA Euro 2016]] play-off against [[Sweden national football team|Sweden]] in November 2015.<ref>{{cite news|title=Denmark announces squad for Euro 2016 qualifying play-offs |url=http://www.globaltimes.cn/content/950467.shtml|accessdate=13 November 2015|publisher=globaltimes.cn|date=3 November 2015}}</ref>
He made his senior debut coming on as a subsistute for [[Kasper Schmeichel]] against Scotland in 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/35862178|title=Scotland 1–0 Denmark|date=29 March 2016|publisher=|via=www.bbc.co.uk}}</ref>
In May 2018 Lössl was named in Denmark's preliminary 35-man [[Denmark national football team|squad]] for the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]] in Russia.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.goal.com/en-gb/amp/news/revealed-every-world-cup-2018-squad-23-man-preliminary-lists/oa0atsduflsv1nsf6oqk576rb|title=Revealed: Every World Cup 2018 squad - 23-man & preliminary lists & when will they be announced? - Goal.com|publisher=}}</ref>
